Austria’s 2011 GDP Forecast Raised a Third Time to 2.5 Percent

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   T i r o n e
-- 
2011-04-01T09:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-01/austria-s-2011-gdp-forecast-raised-a-third-time-to-2-5-percent.html
Austrian exporters have benefitted
from the global economic recovery and will spur higher
production of goods and services this year than previously
forecast, a government-sponsored research group said today.  Austria ’s 2011 gross domestic product, the value of all
goods and services will rise 2.5 percent, the Wifo research
institute said today in an e-mail statement. The Alpine
country’s economy is expected to expand another 2 percent in
2012, Wifo reiterated from earlier forecasts.  It is the third time that Wifo has raised its growth
forecast for Austria in 2011. The group said Dec. 17 that it
expected a 2.2 percent economic expansion. On Sept. 24 it
foresaw 1.9 percent growth.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan Tirone in Vienna at 
 jtirone@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Hertling at   jhertling@bloomberg.net  